HEADWORD: Siphuncle
<hw>Si"phun`cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>siphunculus</ets>, <ets>sipunculus</ets>, dim. of <ets>sipho</ets>.
See <er>Siphon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The tube which runs
through the partitions of chambered cephalopod shells.</def>⟦br⟧
